rComments: His dad jokes are hilarious and make me pay attention. Hes also very knowledgeable, teaches well by making analogies and giving tips and tricks for memorization. I used to hate anything related to sodium potassium pumps but he made that interesting. Overall, really great prof. Exams are fair and reflect material learned in lectures.

I must say he is not fit to teach pharam as simple as that! He is not fun, always distracts me with his super long stories & I must say his slides can definitely need more work. Oh MCQs IDK how he makes them because some are just ridiculous not all but some. If you study you will do good but overall he is not fabulous as he wants to be! #Sorry

It's pharm so looots of memorization but no ridiculously hard questions. Babbles a bit in the pre-recorded lecture but gives information. If you have any issues with content, exam mark, etc., don't hesitate to ask for a meeting/go to office hours as he'll answer any questions or help you with anything. Very kind guy. I didn't open my book once tho
overgoes class time every single lecture and needs to be more concise with his lectures. a lot of stuff he says/adds to slides is just not needed

Professor Leddy is an amazing prof. His lectures are engaging and make a lot of sense which is important for this class. He is super smart but breaks things down so that they are understandable on a basic level and his exams reflect exactly what was taught in class. I would definitely recommend his class!

There's no changing the fact that this is a tough course, but this prof does a really good job of making it as straightforward as possible. He was very accessible outside class which can really help for a course as dense as this. I would never take this course if you don't have to, but if you do this prof is a great choice.

Professor Leddy made one of my hardest classes my most enjoyable class this semester. I looked forward to coming to this class and the way he presents his lectures is amazing and easy to learn from. Some people are saying in the fall semester he was going over his lecture time but he fixed that this semester his lectures respected the class times.

My experience with him was just ok. His explanations are fine but he repeats himself a lot which is annoying. His notes aren't well organized. What was most disappointing was that he did not adapt well to online learning; his lectures were always 2+ hours long instead of 1 hour 20 min. He said he'd make up for it but he never did - liar...
Awesome prof, makes funny dad jokes and is always available to answer questions. Very kind and respectful.

Prof. Leddy cares about his students. Was part of his first english PHA class. He stresses exactly what needs to be done to do well in his class. You could skip class, but he gives such great tips and examples I would not recommend it. Take notes, review and memorize as often as you can. He is very approachable and happy to answer any questions.

Best prof I have ever had. He explains things really well. I would suggest recording his lectures since he doesn't mind just in case you miss certain parts of the lecture. His exams are fair and exactly what he teaches no surprises, just pay attention and make sure you understand what he is talking about. Lots of memorization, but this is pharm!
the best prof at uottawa

Leddy was a great prof and made pharmacology as enjoyable so that it could be. His exams are hard but fair, and he tells the class the difficulty and content for there to be surprises on the exams. He cares about his students and is available through email and office hours. If you have the option to take his class, do it!
Un des meilleur, le cours est bien fait donc pas trop pesant mais serait bien de savoir les different anatomie avant si tu veut acer le cours

BEST PROF I have had at uottawa ! Great lecturer, and gives great examples that makes the material easy to retain. I found the first exam to be harder than the second midterm and final. Passing with an A- is definitely doable. You must invest in the course and gradually study.
Ok prof

Super nice guy and gives excellent lectures. Goes through the material again if you ask him to. However, respiratory physiology can be really tough. (It didn't come easily to me.) So use your resources (textbook, videos, etc.) if you want to ace the final. Fair exam questions and fair marking; you just need to work for that A!
I was  a little surprised, some questions on the exam were more difficult than expected and did not reflect what was emphasized in class.

Loved his lectures, the final exam questions were a bit surprising and different from what expected nevertheless he tried his best during class and was always open to questions. (HSS3342 is a heavy course don't take it unless you have to)

This professors is an amazing professor. Take any class he teaches. He knows exactly what he is talking abot. He is very clear about what he wants us to know for the exam. Do not miss any classes, his exams include what he mentioned in class and what is on the slide. His course requires effort, lots of memorization, but it's very interesting!
Should definitely win an award for best prof! Makes us laugh and enjoy learning Un Prof et une personne super-extraordinaire!!  Tip: You must study for exams.  :)
The best prof of all that teach PHS 3240. He explains very clearly and everything makes sense! Funny and doesn't put you to sleep. Teaches respiratory and his notes are clear enough.

Exceptional prof. Material is not easy at all but he is extremely clear, no tricks on the exams, very very helpful and a very fair grader. The grade you will get in this class will be very representative of the work you put in and it is possible to do well in his classes (A/A+).

Fantastic prof! Down to earth and very knowledgeable. Can explain anything to anyone. Final exam was brutal, but his questions were fair. Beware of the other teachers that teach the course. Pratt and Tuana are useless compared to him. BEST PROF in my 5 years at Uni.
Best prof ever. He knows everything about his subject, he is so nice and very funny. Always a pleasure to be in his class, I hope he got prizes or something for his teaching!

Awesome! Lots of really funny stories that relate to the material that help you remember your notes for the exam (ask about peptobismol and his roommates...). The final exam isn't his fault, there is just LOTS of meds to cover (250).
He is an excellent professor! Quite funny too! He makes hard material easy. His explanations are extremely helpful and clear. LOVED his class!
awesome prof - made the hard stuff much easier
Cool Teacher #1
if there is the nobel prize for teaching it should go to this man!
monsieur John Leddy est un excellent prof qui connait tres bien sa matiere et qui sait comment faire aimer la matiere aux eleves :)
vey very good prof. Knows what he is talking about and explains concepts well.
Very cool teacher!! and super interesting class.
Great guy, and extremely helpful.  Funny and well-organised.
Was candid with the class and never lost energy. Favorite UofO Prof by far.
Great Prof.  Lectures are always great but the notes have room for improvement.
Cutie
Simply the best teacher!!!!
great prof, and cute as a bug's ear
